Package: xtop
Version: 0.25.2-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Installed-Size: 11140
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor that goes beyond traditional
 tools like htop by correlating signals across CPU, memory, IO, network,
 and cgroups to produce ranked root-cause hypotheses with evidence and
 confidence scores.
 .
 Instead of showing raw metrics, xtop answers: What is the bottleneck?
 Who is causing it? How confident are we? What should I do?
 .
 Key features:
  - CLI subcommands: xtop why, xtop top, xtop proc for instant diagnosis
  - Impact scoring: composite per-process impact (CPU/PSI/IO/Mem/Net weighted)
  - Deep per-PID analysis: memory, IO, FDs, network connections
  - Local daemon API: Unix socket for instant subcommand queries
  - CPU flamegraphs: xtop flame <pid> with ASCII renderer
  - Safe autopilot: CPU throttle, process isolation, IO nice with auto-rollback
  - SLO policies: define and monitor service level objectives
  - Application identity intelligence: resolve java/python/node to real app names
  - Modular language runtime detection: JVM, .NET, Python, Node.js, Go
  - JVM intelligence: hsperfdata parsing for GC, heap, threads, class counts
  - .NET Core on Linux: EventPipe diagnostics (GC, threadpool, allocations)
  - Cross-signal correlation: cause-effect detection across domains
  - Multi-resolution ring buffers: 1s + 10s + 60s aggregation
  - SQLite incident persistence with fingerprinting and recurrence tracking
  - eBPF network security intelligence: SYN flood, port scan, DNS tunneling, C2 beacon detection
  - PSI (Pressure Stall Information) pressure tracking
  - Cgroup-aware throttling and limit detection
  - Evidence-based RCA with confidence scoring
  - eBPF probes: off-CPU, IO latency, lock contention, TCP retransmits
  - Sentinel probes: always-on BPF monitoring (drops, resets, OOM, throttle)
  - Watchdog: auto-triggered deep probes on RCA bottleneck detection
  - DiskGuard: filesystem space monitor with auto-contain (SIGSTOP/SIGCONT)
  - Causal chain reconstruction and anomaly onset tracking
